<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>A Correction of Geiger</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Platinum">Platinum</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:56 a.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> A Correction of Geiger<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I read this quote of yours "This game doesn't inherently support sensless killing" and feel the need to correct it in light of my opinions. First off, yes, EverQuest highly promotes random pk'ng. The switch allows only two types of players, -pvp and +pvp. A +pvp can kill everyone, thats just how it is right now whether you are on a pvp server or not. If the restrictions on players on a pvp server become so great, many will go2 -pvp servers, turn on pvp, and just hope they encounter other pvp players. EverQuest at the moment IS NOT a solid atmosphere. The game is not solid enough to say 'ok pvp server do what you want, game will handle' (although it is a beta). Right now power of gm's is still required to keep players actions in line. Whether there is +pvp, -pvp, rules, gm's etc there will still be what are known as "fuqsters", players that only seek the destruction of others. And whether or not they are on a pvp server, believe me if UO is any indication, they will find a way to mess up someone else, screw someone's character, and generally cause havoc. The answer is to create a solid pvp environment, that doesn't rely on other players "role playing" because pk is VERY MUCH roleplaying. Sitting in town hitting "fish" a bunch of times is not role playing, its mindless drone activity. Futhermore, there should also not be so many rules on a pvp server that limit pvp. Players on a PvP server fully understand what they are getting into. Were it up to me I would ask players to design their own version of PvP, then at least I would know what players truely want.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER><EM><A HREF="http://www.gametab.com/eq/align.html" TARGET=_top>ALIGNMENT SYSTEM BABY!!!!</A></EM></P>
